pr_body: Try to set up Github Actions instead of Travis CI
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 687374410, 'comment_body': '@diego-urgell this seems incorrect. According to https://cran.r-project.org/doc/manuals/r-release/R-exts.html#Using-C_002b_002b-code  you should instead use 
```
CXX_STD = CXX17
```
and then R will generate the compiler-specific flags (such as `-std=gnu++17`) that are required to use the C++ 17 standard.
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 4, 14, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'tdhock', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 687392013, 'comment_body': 'Yes, you are right. Originally it was like that but I changed to test if I could "hardcode" the standard. However, even after setting `CXX17`,  it still generates the same error. I will open a new branch to remove all C++14 dependencies and see if the package compiles successfully with g++ that way. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 5, 9, 43, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'diego-urgell', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 687393150, 'comment_body': 'Also, I thought that maybe it was because of the R version, but even after specifying the latest release, the error persists. I also got the same result using an Azure VM, so the problem is likely because of the new C++ features :(', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 5, 13, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'diego-urgell', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 687405823, 'comment_body': "before you remove the C++14 / 17 features, please post to R-package-devel with sufficient details (minimal reproducible example) to explain your problem. R says it supports C++14 / 17, so you should be able to get this to work. (but there may be some missing configuration, or maybe a bug in R)
If you don't get a good response from R-pacakge-devel, it may be appropriate for https://stat.ethz.ch/mailman/listinfo/r-devel", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 5, 47, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'tdhock', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 687406642, 'comment_body': 'also you should try to compile a source code "by hand" using gcc. can you install gcc on your computer? can you try to manually write a command for compiling one of your C++17 files with gcc? If you can get gcc to do it, you should be able to tell R how to generate that command.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 5, 49, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'tdhock', 'type': 'User'}]
